{\b1 \cf24 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb200 
Opinion
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_Ic3e289c8bfed11ec9f24ec7b211d8}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_Ic3e289c8bfed11ec9f24ec7b211d8}
\par 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=h&pubNum=176284&cite=0103381501&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
NORTHCUTT
}}}
\sa200 
\sb200 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa200 \sb200 
, Judge.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\*\bkmkstart co_anchor_Ic3e289cabfed11ec9f24ec7b211d8}{\*\bkmkend co_anchor_Ic3e289cabfed11ec9f24ec7b211d8}
\par 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The issue before us is whether a county property appraiser may require prospective commercial users of the records created in his office to first enter into a licensing agreement. We conclude that he may not. For this reason, we reverse the summary judgment in favor of Abe Skinner, the Collier County Property Appraiser, and remand with directions to enter judgment for Microdecisions, Inc.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The facts in this case are uncontested. Microdecisions compiles data concerning 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_735_873_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_735_873_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*873
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 real estate in south Florida, then sells this product on its website. Its customers can pay to retrieve plats, maps, and information about property values and mortgage encumbrances, among other things. With this purpose in mind, Microdecisions sought copies of Geographic Information Systems (GIS) maps that Skinner created in the course of his official duties. No one disputes that the GIS maps are public records,
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_B00112005630739_ID0ED1AE_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_B00112005630739_ID0ED1AE_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_B00112005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
1
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 but Skinner claimed they were copyrighted under federal law. He refused to permit Microdecisions\rquote  unfettered use of the maps unless it agreed to a licensing agreement that required a royalty payment if the maps were used commercially. Microdecisions filed a petition for writ of mandamus and a declaratory judgment action in circuit court, seeking to compel Skinner to provide the public records unencumbered by the licensing agreement. Skinner filed affirmative defenses, and eventually both parties moved for summary judgment.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F12005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf32 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[1]
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 We review a summary judgment de novo. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=Ib9047f950c5a11d9bc18e8274af85244&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2000356033&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_130&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_130" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Volusia County v. Aberdeen at Ormond Beach, L.P.,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 760 So.2d 126, 130 (Fla.2000)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. The circuit court based its decision to grant Skinner\rquote s summary judgment motion on two of his affirmative defenses. The court\rquote s first ground was that Microdecisions\rquote  claim under Florida\rquote s public records laws was moot. Skinner maintained that after the lawsuit was filed, he sent Microdecisions a set of CD\u8211\'3fROM discs containing the maps. Thus, he argued, Microdecisions\rquote  claim was moot because the company had been given the public records. But the maps were transmitted with a letter that enclosed \u8220\'3fa copy of the Personal Use License Agreement that does not permit commercial use of the data in any manner.\u8221\'3f The license agreement purported to bind the user if the discs were used. Microdecisions was unwilling to agree to the restriction.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F22005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf32 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[2]
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 A case is moot only \u8220\'3fwhen the controversy has been so fully resolved that a judicial determination can have no actual effect.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1985118758&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_1016&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_1016" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Montgomery v. Dep\rquote t of Health & Rehabilitative Servs.,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 468 So.2d 1014, 1016 (Fla. 1st DCA 1985)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Here, Microdecisions sought unconditional access to the public records, including the right to use the records in its business, but Skinner delivered the GIS maps on the condition that they were for personal use only. Therefore, the controversy concerning whether Skinner can validly impose this restriction on the use of the maps remained at issue. The circuit court erred as a matter of law in finding that the public records claim was moot. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1993200805&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_943&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_943" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
WFTV, Inc. v. Robbins,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 625 So.2d 941, 943 (Fla. 4th DCA 1993)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (reversing the denial of a petition for writ of mandamus as moot when the issues presented were still live and the parties had a legally cognizable interest in the outcome).
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F32005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf32 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[3]
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The circuit court\rquote s second basis for the summary judgment was that the case involved a copyright issue that should be decided by a federal court. Skinner\rquote s affirmative defenses claimed that Microdecisions\rquote  
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_735_874_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_735_874_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*874
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 legal actions were actually an attempt to litigate his right to copyright the maps and that federal courts had exclusive jurisdiction over copyright actions under 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=28USCAS1338&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RB&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_8b3b0000958a4" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
28 U.S.C. \u167\'3f 1338(a)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Early in the suit, Skinner filed a notice of removal to the United States District Court for the Middle District of Florida, again contending that the federal court had exclusive jurisdiction. But that court remanded the case to state court. The order of remand pointed out that the presence or absence of federal question jurisdiction is governed by the \u8220\'3fwell-pleaded complaint\u8221\'3f rule. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I6b228e169c2511d9bc61beebb95be672&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1998057505&pubNum=0000708&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Rivet v. Regions Bank of La.,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 522 U.S. 470, 474\u8211\'3f75, 118 S.Ct. 921, 139 L.Ed.2d 912 (1998)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. The district court noted:
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li200 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li200 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li1000 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri800 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li1000 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The well-pleaded complaint in this case alleges that the documents are public records to which the Property Appraiser must allow access pursuant to Florida law, without further restriction. Nothing about the claims in the Complaint arise out of federal law in general or the Copyright Act in particular, and they do not satisfy the test articulated by the Eleventh Circuit. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=Ic8803d0596fd11d9a707f4371c9c34f0&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1993197991&pubNum=0000506&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_506_1412&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_506_1412" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Sullivan v. Naturalis, Inc.,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 5 F.3d 1410, 1412 (11th Cir.1993)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa400 \sb600 
.
\par 
}
}
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2009653965&pubNum=0004031&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Microdecisions, Inc. v. Skinner,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 No. 2:02\u8211\'3fcv\u8211\'3f639\u8211\'3fFTM\u8211\'3f29DNF (M.D.Fla. Feb. 5, 2003)
}}}
\sb200 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb200 
 (unpublished order). It concluded that Microdecisions\rquote  complaint did not state causes of action that arose under federal copyright law.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
The federal court\rquote s well-reasoned order is supported by Florida law as well. The First District addressed similar facts in 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1994107802&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Department of Health & Rehabilitative Services v. Southpointe Pharmacy,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 636 So.2d 1377 (Fla. 1st DCA 1994)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. In that case, the pharmacy filed a petition for writ of mandamus seeking documents pursuant to Florida\rquote s public records law, 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=ND1CBE7B0DE8511EB8F99D38EC757D1E4&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000006&cite=FLSTS119.07&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
section 119.07, Florida Statutes
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. As in this case, the complaint did not allege a cause of action under the federal copyright law, but the public entity defended on the ground that the documents were copyrighted. The 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Southpointe
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 court held that under the federal well-pleaded complaint rule a copyright 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
defense
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 does not defeat state court jurisdiction. 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1994107802&pubNum=735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_1380&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_1380" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
636 So.2d at 1380.
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 As such, the Florida state courts had jurisdiction over the matter.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
This case, like 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Southpointe,
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 arises under Florida\rquote s public records law, not under federal copyright law. Copyright is not an essential element of Microdecisions\rquote  claim. As such, as a matter of both federal and Florida law, the circuit court erred when it determined this controversy belonged in federal court. And, as we have previously discussed, Microdecisions\rquote  public records claim is not moot.
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Accordingly, we reverse the judgment in favor of Skinner.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F42005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf32 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[4]
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The issue presented here is purely one of law; the facts are undisputed. We therefore examine whether the circuit court erred in denying Microdecisions\rquote  cross-motion for summary judgment. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2004471035&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_499&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_499" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Bridgham v. Skrzynski,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 873 So.2d 496, 499 (Fla. 2d DCA 2004)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
; 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1982146721&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_643&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_643" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Royal Neth. Realty, Inc. v. Ross,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 421 So.2d 642, 643 (Fla. 3d DCA 1982)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. We hold that Skinner has no authority to assert copyright protection in the GIS maps, which are public records. Accordingly, Microdecisions was entitled to summary judgment as a matter of law.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F52005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf32 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[5]
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Congress explicitly denied copyright protection to works of the United States government, 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=N1F5A85F0FA9611F08DDCD5D37DBB84CC&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=17USCAS105&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
17 U.S.C. \u167\'3f 105
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, but it did not restrict state governments in that regard. \u8220\'3fWorks of state governments are therefore left available for copyright protection by the state or the individual author, depending on state law and policy, and subject to exceptions dictated by public policy....\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I8c5446db922c11d9bdd1cfdd544ca3a4&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1980135612&pubNum=0000350&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_350_735&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_350_735" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Bldg. Officials & Code Adm\rquote rs v. Code Tech, Inc.,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 628 F.2d 730, 735\u8211\'3f36 (1st Cir.1980)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
; 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
see also 
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I9ca2079b79bb11d9bf29e2067ad74e5b&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2001635360&pubNum=0000506&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_506_188&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_506_188" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
County of Suffolk, N.Y. v. First Am. Real Estate 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_735_875_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_735_875_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*875
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Solutions,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 261 F.3d 179, 188 (2d Cir.2001)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Thus, Florida law determines whether Skinner may claim a copyright in his office\rquote s creations.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In Florida, a citizen\rquote s right of access to public records is protected both by the Florida Constitution and the Florida statutes. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=N143E2D307E5511DA8F1DA64F3D0F013D&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000245&cite=FLCNART1S24&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Art. I, \u167\'3f 24(a), Fla. Const. (1992)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (the \u8220\'3fSunshine Amendment\u8221\'3f); 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000006&cite=FLSTS119.01&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u167\'3f 119.01, Fla. Stat. (2002)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Although the Sunshine Amendment was not adopted until 1992, Florida has a long-standing legal tradition of permitting access to its public records. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2002706623&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_713&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_713" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In re Report & Recommendations of Judicial Mgmt. Council of Fla. on Privacy & Elec. Access to Court Records,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 832 So.2d 712, 713 (Fla.2002)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (stating that in Florida \u8220\'3fopen access to public records is both a constitutional right and a cornerstone of our political culture\u8221\'3f). Our first public records law was enacted in 1892. \u167\'3f\u167\'3f 1390, 1391, Fla. Stat. (Rev.1892). Its existing progeny, 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000006&cite=FLSTS119.01&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=SP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_f1c50000821b0" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
section 119.01(1)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, declares the policy that \u8220\'3fall state, county, and municipal records shall be open for personal inspection by any person.\u8221\'3f
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F62005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf32 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[6]
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The custodian of any public record must furnish a copy of the record upon payment of the fee prescribed by law, generally the cost of reproduction. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=ND1CBE7B0DE8511EB8F99D38EC757D1E4&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000006&cite=FLSTS119.07&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=SP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_9f800000f2221" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u167\'3f 119.07(1)(a)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. A requester\rquote s motive for seeking a copy of documents is irrelevant. 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1980136324&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_278&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_278" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
News\u8211\'3fPress Pub. Co. v. Gadd,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 388 So.2d 276, 278 (Fla. 2d DCA 1980)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Moreover, the fact that a person seeking access to public records wishes to use them in a commercial enterprise does not alter his or her rights under Florida\rquote s public records law. Since 1905, it has been clear that public records may be used in a commercial, profit-making business without the payment of additional fees. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I1d00dd960c6011d9bc18e8274af85244&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
