{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1905000121&pubNum=0000734&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
State ex rel. Davis v. McMillan,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 49 Fla. 243, 38 So. 666 (1905)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
McMillan
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 interpreted the 1892 statute, which provided that public records shall be open to the public \u8220\'3ffor the purpose of inspection thereof, and of making extracts therefrom.\u8221\'3f 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I1d00dd960c6011d9bc18e8274af85244&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1905000121&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Id.
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 at 667.
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 In that case the clerk of the court had argued that he could prevent employees of an abstract company from taking extracts from the public records to be compiled and sold unless the company paid him large amounts for inspecting the records and extracting them. The court held that the public records law forbade such a demand for fees. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I1d00dd960c6011d9bc18e8274af85244&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1905000121&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Id.
}
}}}
\par 
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_hn_anchor_F72005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b1 \cf32 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
[7]
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 To be sure, the legislature may exempt specific public records from the public records law. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See 
}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1987051955&pubNum=0000735&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_735_1118&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_735_1118" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Bevan v. Wanicka,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 505 So.2d 1116, 1118 (Fla. 2d DCA 1987)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. The Sunshine Amendment permits the legislature, by two-thirds vote, to enact exemptions for public records, but only after specially defining a public necessity and narrowly tailoring the exemption to that necessity. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=N143E2D307E5511DA8F1DA64F3D0F013D&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000245&cite=FLCNART1S24&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Art. I, \u167\'3f 24(c), Fla. Const
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. Accordingly, the legislature has allowed restrictions on the unlimited access to some public records by enacting specific statutes authorizing certain agencies to obtain copyrights in particular circumstances. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See, e.g.,
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=N8C4BF8F068D411F0816DDF39D03BB8C1&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000006&cite=FLSTS24.105&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=SP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_f19d0000e06d3" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u167\'3f 24.105(10), Fla. Stat. (2003)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (authorizing the Department of the Lottery to hold copyrights); 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000006&cite=FLSTS601.101&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u167\'3f 601.101, Fla. Stat. (2003)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (permitting the Department of Citrus to hold legal title to copyrights); 
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000006&cite=FLSTS1004.23&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=LQ&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u167\'3f 1004.23, Fla. Stat. (2002)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 (authorizing universities to secure copyrights in certain works). No statute authorizes a county property appraiser to hold a copyright.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Additionally, the legislature has specifically permitted certain categories of public records to be copyrighted. Section 119.084 permits agencies to acquire and hold copyrights for data processing software the agencies have created.
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
{\*\bkmkstart co_fnRef_B00222005630739_ID0EU1AG_1}{\*\bkmkend co_fnRef_B00222005630739_ID0EU1AG_1}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "#co_footnote_B00222005630739_1" }{\fldrslt 
{\super \b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs16 \sa0 \sb0 
2
}}}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 The 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\*\bkmkstart co_pp_sp_735_876_1}{\*\bkmkend co_pp_sp_735_876_1}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
*876
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 staff analysis of the Senate bill that created section 119.084 recognized that a law permitting copyright protection of public records creates a public records exemption as contemplated in the Sunshine Amendment. Therefore a statement of public necessity was required under the Sunshine Amendment and was included in the bill. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Fla. S. Comm. on Comprehensive Planning, CS for SB 2220 (2001) Staff Analysis (Apr. 10, 2001) (on file with comm.).
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In his brief, Skinner claims that nothing in the Florida Statutes precludes a constitutional officer such as himself from holding a copyright on the GIS maps. He misconstrues the interplay between the federal copyright act and Florida\rquote s public records laws. The copyright act gives the holder the exclusive rights to reproduce and distribute a work and to authorize others to do so. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=N64EE8AE0A06711D8B8FABFF7D35FC9C0&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=17USCAS106&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RB&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_f1c50000821b0" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
17 U.S.C. \u167\'3f 106(1)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
, 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=N64EE8AE0A06711D8B8FABFF7D35FC9C0&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000546&cite=17USCAS106&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RB&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_d08f0000f5f67" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
(3)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. As such, a copyright owner may refuse to provide copies of the work or may charge whatever fee he wants for copies of the work or a license to use the work. The Florida public records law, on the other hand, requires State and local agencies to make their records available to the public for the cost of reproduction. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=ND1CBE7B0DE8511EB8F99D38EC757D1E4&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=L&pubNum=1000006&cite=FLSTS119.07&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=SP&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_9f800000f2221" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u167\'3f 119.07(1)(a)
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
. This mandate overrides a governmental agency\rquote s ability to claim a copyright in its work unless the legislature has expressly authorized a public records exemption. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
See
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=N143E2D307E5511DA8F1DA64F3D0F013D&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
