{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=2001635360&pubNum=506&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_506_195&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_506_195" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
261 F.3d at 195.
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 But New York law is not Florida law. We offer no opinion on the federal circuit\rquote s analysis because it simply has no application in this case. Each state may determine whether the works of its governmental entities may be copyrighted. 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://1.next.westlaw.com/Link/RelatedInformation/Flag?documentGuid=I8c5446db922c11d9bdd1cfdd544ca3a4&transitionType=InlineKeyCiteFlags&originationContext=docHeaderFlag&Rank=0&ppcid=35cdb2e9c8824ddbbd68818b07961b24&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)" }{\fldrslt 
{\*\shppict {\pict \pngblip \picw16 \pich16 \picwgoal255 \pichgoal255 }}}}
}
{\field {\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://www.westlaw.com/Link/Document/FullText?findType=Y&serNum=1980135612&pubNum=350&originatingDoc=I27afd7e743d911d98915dbcd77ee80bc&refType=RP&fi=co_pp_sp_350_735&originationContext=document&vr=3.0&rs=cblt1.0&transitionType=DocumentItem&contextData=(sc.CustomDigest)#co_pp_sp_350_735" }{\fldrslt 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Code Tech,
}
}
{\b0 \cf23 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 628 F.2d at 735\u8211\'3f36;
}}}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
see also
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 1 Melville and David Nimmer, 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \i1 \fs20 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i1 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Nimmer on Copyright
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 \u167\'3f 5.14, at 5\u8211\'3f106 (2002). As we have explained, Florida\rquote s Constitution and its statutes do not permit public records to be copyrighted unless the legislature specifically states they can be.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Accordingly, we hold that Skinner cannot prevail on his defense of copyright. Microdecisions is entitled to summary judgment as a matter of law. We reverse the summary judgment entered in Skinner\rquote s favor and remand with directions to enter summary judgment in favor of Microdecisions.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Reversed and remanded.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf21 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
}
}
